  "name": "ZLEMA_CMO_ATR_Trend_Follower",
  "description": "This algorithm employs a Zero-Lag Exponential Moving Average (ZLEMA) combined with the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) to identify trend direction on a 4-hour timeframe. It utilizes the Average True Range (ATR) for dynamic position sizing, entering long positions when the close price crosses above the ZLEMA and the CMO exceeds +40, and short positions under the opposite conditions.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python using a 4-hour timeframe that combines a Zero-Lag Exponential Moving Average (ZLEMA) with the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) and the Average True Range (ATR) for dynamic position sizing. Entry rule: enter a long position when the close price crosses above the 34-period ZLEMA and the 14-period CMO is above +40; enter short when the close crosses below the 34-period ZLEMA and CMO is below -40. Exit long positions when price closes below the 21-period ZLEMA or the CMO drops below +10; exit shorts when price closes above the 21-period ZLEMA or the CMO rises above -10. Use a volatility-adjusted stop loss set at 1.5\u00d7 ATR(14) from entry price. Implement position sizing proportional to 2% of capital divided by current ATR value to adapt risk dynamically. Ensure the algorithm avoids signals during sideways markets by confirming that the Bollinger Bands Width (20, 2) exceeds its 50-period moving average before entering trades.",
